#N canvas 50 50 800 970 10;
#X text 20 15 sequencer.pd v2 - NES Triangle channel + 8-step sequencer (C major arpeggio);
#X text 20 40 Listens for: /unity/tempo (int ms) \, /unity/playseq (0/1);
#X text 20 65 Outputs: audio signal (mono) via [outlet~];
#X text 20 100 INTERNAL CONTROL BUSES (set from MockMidterm.pd \, tempo defaulted via loadbang on right):;
#X text 30 125 osctempo : metro interval in ms (default 250 = 240 BPM 16ths);
#X text 30 147 oscplayseq : 0 to stop the sequencer \, 1 to start it;
#X text 20 180 TECHNIQUES (NES-authentic):;
#X text 30 205 - Triangle: [phasor~] -> [-~ 0.5] -> [abs~] -> [*~ 4] -> [-~ 1] = bipolar triangle wave;
#X text 30 227 - Sequencer: [metro] -> [f] + [+ 1] -> [mod 8] -> [select] = looping 8-step counter;
#X text 30 249 - Pattern: 0 4 7 12 7 4 0 7 semitones above C3 (NES bass-line arpeggio);
#X text 30 271 - Per-step amp envelope: 0.6 10 \, 0 150 80 = articulated notes \, click-free;
#X obj 60 320 r osctempo;
#X obj 250 320 r oscplayseq;
#X obj 60 360 metro 250;
#X obj 60 400 f;
#X obj 150 400 + 1;
#X obj 60 440 mod 8;
#X obj 60 480 select 0 1 2 3 4 5 6 7;
